Module org.nasdanika.egineering
Package org.nasdanika.engineering

Interface IssueCategory

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Adaptable, Aim, Alignable, EObject, Marked, Marked, ModelElement, ModelElement, NamedElement, NamedElement, Notifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    IssueCategoryImpl
    public interface IssueCategory
extends Aim
    A representation of the model object 'Issue Category'.

    The following features are supported:

    • Weight
    • Issues
    • Cumulative
    • Allocations
    • Children
    See Also:
    EngineeringPackage.getIssueCategory()

      • getWeight

        double getWeight()
        Returns the value of the 'Weight' attribute. Category relative importance. Can be used to allocate issues to increments in a balanced way.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Weight' attribute.
        See Also:
        setWeight(double), EngineeringPackage.getIssueCategory_Weight()

      • getIssues

        Returns the value of the 'Issues' reference list. The list contents are of type Issue. Issues in the category.

        See Also:

      • isCumulative

        boolean isCumulative()
        Returns the value of the 'Cumulative' attribute. If true, unused category weight "capacity" is carried over to future increments and overused is subtracted from future increments. This allow low-weight categories to accumulate weight over time.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Cumulative' attribute.
        See Also:
        setCumulative(boolean), EngineeringPackage.getIssueCategory_Cumulative()

      • getAllocations

        EList<Allocation> getAllocations()
        Returns the value of the 'Allocations' reference list. The list contents are of type Allocation. It is bidirectional and its opposite is 'Category'. Allocations for this category.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Allocations' reference list.
        See Also:
        EngineeringPackage.getIssueCategory_Allocations(), Allocation.getCategory()

      • getChildren

        EList<IssueCategory> getChildren()
        Returns the value of the 'Children' containment reference list. The list contents are of type IssueCategory. Issue categories can form a hierarchy.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Children' containment reference list.
        See Also:
        EngineeringPackage.getIssueCategory_Children()
